Project dstate (C:/dev/dstate): an agent-owned, self-evolving DAG+FSM state library in TypeScript on Bun. Event-sourced spine = append-only hash-chained log in bun:sqlite (WAL); nodes/edges/zones/stats/cursor are a deterministic projection of it. One graph is simultaneously memory (node payloads), policy (guard DSL + soft/hard enforcement + safe transition zones), and intuition (edge stats -> UCB suggest). Public surface is the DState facade in src/index.ts. Verify with `bunx tsc --noEmit`, `bun test` (66 unit tests), `bun test.js` (integration witness), `bun run bench` (perf). Runs on bun (bun:sqlite); the gm exec_js spool verb runs under node and cannot import the bun: scheme, so bun-native checks use `bun -e`.